assistant to extend your stay.

65
00:07:33,790 --> 00:07:34,800
Come to think of it.

66
00:07:35,960 --> 00:07:38,280
Your assistant’s voice was so loud.

67
00:07:39,240 --> 00:07:42,790
I could still hear her refusing
even from where I stood.

68
00:07:47,100 --> 00:07:48,409
But I gave my word.

69
00:07:51,210 --> 00:07:51,930
It’s okay.

70
00:07:54,650 --> 00:07:55,260
I’m used to it.

71
00:08:11,820 --> 00:08:12,720
Let me ask again.

72
00:08:13,350 --> 00:08:14,360
Can I choose my return date?

73
00:08:15,500 --> 00:08:16,580
No!

74
00:08:16,840 --> 00:08:19,420
No means no.
You must return today.

75
00:08:22,680 --> 00:08:24,360
- But…
- Listen to me, P’ Rak.

76
00:08:24,400 --> 00:08:25,800
You have a meeting tomorrow.

77
00:08:27,720 --> 00:08:29,510
You’re returning today, aren’t you?

78
00:08:29,540 --> 00:08:30,810
Aren’t you?

79
00:08:31,340 --> 00:08:33,590
You didn't forget that you
had a meeting with the agency

80
00:08:33,620 --> 00:08:35,380
handling your foreign copyrights, did you?

81
00:08:35,760 --> 00:08:38,039
They informed us last month
that they were coming to Thailand.

82
00:08:38,320 --> 00:08:40,340
And you said you could make it.

83
00:08:40,650 --> 00:08:42,600
You can’t back out on me now.

84
00:08:42,890 --> 00:08:45,420
Besides, you remember
they've just sold the copyrights

85
00:08:45,450 --> 00:08:47,150
