241
00:20:30,800 --> 00:20:31,720
Hold on.

242
00:20:31,750 --> 00:20:32,360
Go home.

243
00:20:33,600 --> 00:20:35,300
- P’ Rak!
- I’m sleepy.

244
00:20:35,610 --> 00:20:37,000
- I’m still talking.
- Leave now.

245
00:20:37,460 --> 00:20:38,270
P’ Rak.

246
00:20:39,120 --> 00:20:40,560
You really need to think this through.

247
00:20:40,810 --> 00:20:43,970
You’ve only known him for two weeks.
You can’t take him in like this.

248
00:20:44,540 --> 00:20:46,680
We don’t know who he is
or if we can trust him.

249
00:20:46,990 --> 00:20:48,290
Besides.

250
00:20:51,830 --> 00:20:53,550
What if he’s got something like...

251
00:20:56,710 --> 00:20:59,300
What if he’s carrying something?

252
00:21:02,410 --> 00:21:03,700
You mean STDs?

253
00:21:12,120 --> 00:21:13,840
You’ve got a good point there.

254
00:21:16,030 --> 00:21:17,150
I know, right?

255
00:21:19,050 --> 00:21:21,290
Then take him to the hospital
tomorrow to get tested.

256
00:21:21,310 --> 00:21:21,790
What?!

257
00:21:22,160 --> 00:21:24,690
Oww, my ears are bleeding.

258
00:21:25,370 --> 00:21:26,420
I’m getting sleepy.

259
00:21:26,460 --> 00:21:27,870
Come on, go home now.
It’s late.

260
00:21:27,900 --> 00:21:30,260
- No.
- You should leave now.

261
00:21:30,400 --> 00:21:33,590
And make sure you get him
tested tomorrow, okay?

262
00:21:35,330 --> 00:21:36,260
Why does it have to be me?

263
00:21:38,520 --> 00:21:39,170
