to let you in my room, are you?

275
00:22:20,530 --> 00:22:22,160
You're free to sleep
in any room you want.

276
00:22:22,930 --> 00:22:24,320
Or sleep on the couch, if you’d like.

277
00:22:25,790 --> 00:22:28,860
Or if you want to sleep in
the bathroom, that’s up to you.

278
00:22:30,740 --> 00:22:32,790
But you must never enter my room.

279
00:22:35,860 --> 00:22:36,590
I’m sleepy.

280
00:22:37,300 --> 00:22:39,640
You can take the suitcases
upstairs tomorrow.

281
00:23:55,810 --> 00:23:56,350
Empty.

282
00:24:11,380 --> 00:24:12,760
Don’t they eat or something?

283
00:24:18,310 --> 00:24:19,350
At least they’ve got coffee.

284
00:24:37,090 --> 00:24:37,680
What’s up?

285
00:24:39,070 --> 00:24:41,500
Don’t you “What’s up” me.
Where are you?

286
00:24:44,070 --> 00:24:44,730
Bangkok.

287
00:24:45,060 --> 00:24:45,740
Ai P’ Mut!

288
00:24:46,380 --> 00:24:48,600
You really jumped onto the boat
and followed P’ Rak back?

289
00:24:49,000 --> 00:24:51,420
Did you know the whole
island’s buzzing with gossip?

290
00:24:51,960 --> 00:24:53,440
They say you eloped with P’ Rak.

291
00:24:53,530 --> 00:24:56,640
Can you believe how many people
showed up at my place this morning?

292
00:24:56,660 --> 00:25:00,700
Even folks from across the island rushed
over by boat to my place this morning.

293
00:25:01,570 --> 00:25:02,520
I was baffled.

294
00:25:03,410 --> 00:25:05,400
No matter how much you love money

295
00:25:05,990 --> 00:25:08,800
I argued that you're not that greedy.

296
00:25:10,780 --> 00:25:12,560
And why didn’t you take me with you?

297
00:25:13,050 --> 00:25:15,180
I wanna go to Bangkok too, you know.

298
00:25:15,350 --> 00:25:18,130
So, you’re calling me to say
you wanted to tag along?

299
00:25:18,430 --> 00:25:19,240
Damn right!

300
00:25:19,980 --> 00:25:21,110
You little shit.

301
00:25:22,300 --> 00:25:23,240
When are you coming back?

302
00:25:25,010 --> 00:25:25,680
Can’t say.

303
00:25:26,690 --> 00:25:27,650
Haven't made any plans.

304
00:25:28,350 --> 00:25:30,040
Are you really out of your mind, P’ Mut?

305
00:25:30,540 --> 00:25:31,590
I’m perfectly sane.

306
00:25:33,600 --> 00:25:34,360
By the way, Ai Palm.

307
00:25:35,190 --> 00:25:36,220
Head over to my place.

308
00:25:36,850 --> 00:25:38,410
I'll list out what I need.

309
00:25:38,510 --> 00:25:40,830
I'll give you the address so
you can send everything to me.

310
00:25:41,000 --> 00:25:43,290
You’re now living a fancy life
while I’m left behind.

311
00:25:44,300 --> 00:25:45,260
I’ll wire you money.

312
00:25:46,310 --> 00:25:47,930
Okay, alrighty then!

313
00:25:48,440 --> 00:25:49,880
You’re the best, P’ Mut.

314
00:25:50,230 --> 00:25:52,510
Alright, call me when you get there.

315
00:25:52,710 --> 00:25:53,680
I’m going to the hospital now.

316
00:25:53,930 --> 00:25:54,470
What?

317
00:25:54,890 --> 00:25:56,020
Didn’t you say you weren’t crazy?

318
00:25:57,310 --> 00:25:58,120
I’m completely normal.

319
00:25:58,810 --> 00:26:02,520
But we’ve got a snoozy cat and
a paranoid mouse in the house.

320
00:26:02,700 --> 00:26:03,350
I’m hanging up.

321
00:26:18,250 --> 00:26:19,040
What do I do?

322
00:26:58,410 --> 00:27:00,030
I won’t screw Khun Tongrak here.

323
00:27:00,730 --> 00:27:01,940
Don’t use the word “screw”!

324
00:27:01,970 --> 00:27:03,520
- Then…
- Don’t you say that word!

325
00:27:04,950 --> 00:27:05,870
Don’t!

326
00:27:13,540 --> 00:27:14,230
P’ Rak.

327
00:27:15,250 --> 00:27:16,390
Wake up now.

328
00:27:17,870 --> 00:27:19,360
You have a meeting to attend.

329
00:27:19,640 --> 00:27:20,950
Don’t whine.

330
00:27:21,310 --> 00:27:22,390
Get up now.

331
00:27:23,020 --> 00:27:24,540
Come on, P’ Rak!

332
00:27:24,560 --> 00:27:25,520
(Satapornbooks)

333
00:27:37,700 --> 00:27:38,700
Oh, P’ Rak!

334
00:27:40,550 --> 00:27:42,480
Please give it some more thought.

335
00:27:43,130 --> 00:27:45,170
This is a serious matter.

336
00:27:47,460 --> 00:27:49,400
Please, P’ Rak.

337
00:27:54,960 --> 00:27:57,200
This is different from what P’ Connor did.

338
00:27:57,940 --> 00:27:59,620
I admit I’ve heard that...

339
00:28:00,180 --> 00:28:03,160
P’ Connor used to pay for sex.

340
00:28:04,350 --> 00:28:06,490
But he did it occasionally.

341
00:28:06,640 --> 00:28:09,340
And now he's already in a relationship.

342
00:28:10,630 --> 00:28:12,070
But it’s still different.

343
00:28:12,120 --> 00:28:15,120
You bought Mahasamut
from the South and took him in.

344
00:28:15,830 --> 00:28:17,510
This isn't far from being occasional.

345
00:28:20,290 --> 00:28:22,820
Now you’re responsible
for a complete stranger

346
00:28:22,850 --> 00:28:24,290
and we don’t know if he can be trusted.

347
00:28:24,320 --> 00:28:24,880
Kaimook.

348
00:28:28,580 --> 00:28:30,790
The person Connor paid for is now his wife.

349
00:28:35,500 --> 00:28:38,080
Do you think Mahasamut
will be the one for you?

350
00:28:38,110 --> 00:28:38,980
No.

351
00:28:41,980 --> 00:28:43,250
I’ve made up my mind.

352
00:28:44,420 --> 00:28:46,000
Are you saying I made a bad move?

353
00:28:51,090 --> 00:28:51,600
Well?

354
00:28:55,440 --> 00:28:58,070
So, what are you going to do next?

355
00:29:19,950 --> 00:29:21,540
I need my work schedule updated.

356
00:29:22,600 --> 00:29:23,290
Got it.

357
00:29:23,700 --> 00:29:24,890
Should I send it today?

358
00:29:25,650 --> 00:29:27,350
The medical examination
report’s on the table.

359
00:29:46,190 --> 00:29:47,230
Can you make sense of it?

360
00:29:47,730 --> 00:29:48,230
No.

361
00:29:48,740 --> 00:29:49,870
I've never taken this kind of test.

362
00:29:50,200 --> 00:29:51,390
I’m clean.

363
00:29:52,900 --> 00:29:53,840
It’s in case…

364
00:29:55,080 --> 00:29:55,940
We’re out of condoms.

365
00:30:00,540 --> 00:30:01,670
There’s nothing going on.

366
00:30:01,980 --> 00:30:04,350
You have no idea
what P’ Rak's smile means.

367
00:30:05,040 --> 00:30:07,410
You know nothing, Ai Mook! Nothing!

368
00:30:08,780 --> 00:30:10,160
How about we try...

369
00:30:10,770 --> 00:30:12,210
barebacking next time?

370
00:30:12,240 --> 00:30:13,080
No way!

371
00:30:13,960 --> 00:30:15,440
You absolutely can’t do that.

372
00:30:16,640 --> 00:30:19,820
And who even talks
about this stuff in public?

373
00:30:20,130 --> 00:30:22,060
Cut it out with all that dirty talk!

374
00:30:24,740 --> 00:30:27,460
No subordinates want to
hear about their boss' sex life.

375
00:30:27,880 --> 00:30:28,530
P’ Rak.

376
00:30:29,250 --> 00:30:30,440
Can you believe him?

377
00:30:32,940 --> 00:30:37,140
Please think twice about having
someone like him live with you.

378
00:30:37,610 --> 00:30:38,970
You heard what he said to me.

379
00:30:39,400 --> 00:30:42,280
I was speaking to Khun Tongrak,
not you, Khun Mook.

380
00:30:45,640 --> 00:30:48,180
You’re really rude.

381
00:30:48,600 --> 00:30:49,750
Let’s try it next time.

382
00:30:50,870 --> 00:30:51,680
What?

383
00:30:58,800 --> 00:30:59,390
Nothing.

384
00:30:59,820 --> 00:31:00,750
You know nothing.

385
00:31:01,090 --> 00:31:02,730
Okay, Ai Mook.
Pull yourself together.

386
00:31:04,000 --> 00:31:06,240
You need to review all
the English contract papers

387
00:31:06,260 --> 00:31:08,290
summarize them, and send them to P’ Rak.

388
00:31:08,510 --> 00:31:12,900
Call the publisher to discuss
the cover design for the new novel.

389
00:31:12,920 --> 00:31:16,370
P’ Rak wants a Chinese artist
with a sharp line art.

390
00:31:16,520 --> 00:31:17,100
But…

391
00:31:17,800 --> 00:31:19,100
Korean art is cute too.

392
00:31:20,290 --> 00:31:21,000
I’m torn.

393
00:31:24,240 --> 00:31:25,020
I’m going to shower.

394
00:31:26,030 --> 00:31:26,640
I’m hot.

395
00:31:29,550 --> 00:31:31,090
P’ Rak, don’t go.

396
00:31:36,100 --> 00:31:36,560
Hey!

397
00:31:36,850 --> 00:31:37,770
Look, Mister.

398
00:31:38,360 --> 00:31:39,450
Who allowed you to use the kitchen?

399
00:31:41,260 --> 00:31:42,160
I’m hungry.

400
00:31:43,100 --> 00:31:45,460
If you don’t let me cook,
am I gonna have to eat raw pork?

401
00:31:46,460 --> 00:31:49,000
Haven’t you heard eating raw pork
makes you lose your hearing?

402
00:31:49,650 --> 00:31:50,850
That’s not what I meant.

403
00:31:51,500 --> 00:31:53,400
Who eats raw pork anyway?

404
00:31:54,610 --> 00:31:56,870
I mean, why aren’t you ordering takeout?

405
00:31:58,140 --> 00:31:59,380
It’s cheaper to cook.

406
00:32:06,160 --> 00:32:08,320
P’ Rak doesn’t eat this kind of food.

407
00:32:10,070 --> 00:32:10,790
Why?

408
00:32:11,290 --> 00:32:12,670
It's food too, you know.

409
00:32:12,920 --> 00:32:15,170
Or does Khun Tongrak
live on oil instead of food?

410
00:32:30,130 --> 00:32:32,580
Read through everything.
Ask me about the part you don’t get.

411
00:32:33,310 --> 00:32:33,890
What’s this?

412
00:32:35,020 --> 00:32:38,100
The cohabitation agreement
between P' Rak and you.

413
00:32:38,880 --> 00:32:43,620
If there's anything you disagree with
or want to modify, just let me know.

414
00:32:54,630 --> 00:32:56,010
Have you finally accepted me?

415
00:32:58,960 --> 00:32:59,620
No.

416
00:33:00,190 --> 00:33:01,640
But P’ Rak’s made up his mind.

417
00:33:12,350 --> 00:33:16,600
The content mostly outlines
what P' Rak and you need to fulfill.

418
00:33:16,880 --> 00:33:18,870
P’ Rak will be taking care of the expenses.

419
00:33:18,920 --> 00:33:22,610
And you’re not allowed to do anything
that goes against P’ Rak’s wishes.

420
00:33:27,840 --> 00:33:30,510
"The agreement will terminate
whenever Khun Rak wishes."

421
00:33:31,920 --> 00:33:35,140
Does this part imply Khun
Tongrak’s and my relationship?

422
00:33:36,220 --> 00:33:36,940
Yes.

423
00:33:49,410 --> 00:33:51,970
What if I tell you that I refuse to go?

424
00:33:56,140 --> 00:33:56,900
You can’t.

425
00:33:57,720 --> 00:33:58,790
It’s been decided.

426
00:33:58,880 --> 00:33:59,620
Which means…

427
00:34:00,650 --> 00:34:03,700
Khun Tongrak can kick me out
whenever he's had enough of me.

428
00:34:04,360 --> 00:34:05,310
You've got it right.

429
00:34:09,330 --> 00:34:10,810
Apart from...

430
00:34:11,909 --> 00:34:15,179
the mandatory requirements,
I can change anything for you.

431
00:34:16,110 --> 00:34:19,130
P' Rak says if you want to
study, he'll support you.

432
00:34:19,230 --> 00:34:21,010
Let me know if there’s
anything you want to do.

433
00:34:21,630 --> 00:34:23,100
P’ Rak will back you up in everything.

434
00:34:23,250 --> 00:34:26,989
But you absolutely mustn’t
neglect the mandatory requirements.

435
00:34:27,120 --> 00:34:29,190
Especially the clause that forbids love.

436
00:34:29,210 --> 00:34:30,100
Works for me.

437
00:34:32,780 --> 00:34:33,699
Then let’s move on.

438
00:34:33,949 --> 00:34:36,610
P’ Rak wants to know how much
compensation you’re looking for.

439
00:34:36,850 --> 00:34:38,909
Do you prefer monthly or weekly?

440
00:34:39,100 --> 00:34:42,400
P' Rak proposes to pay on a monthly basis.

441
00:34:42,699 --> 00:34:44,770
Living expenses will be covered separately.

442
00:34:44,880 --> 00:34:48,030
If there's anything else you need,
feel free to let me know.

443
00:34:48,429 --> 00:34:52,630
These expenses won't be
deducted from your compensation.

444
00:34:55,480 --> 00:34:58,620
Do writers typically earn high income?

445
00:35:02,250 --> 00:35:04,250
P’ Rak isn’t just a writer.

446
00:35:05,450 --> 00:35:08,440
He receives income from various sources.

447
00:35:10,580 --> 00:35:11,640
I’m just rich.

448
00:35:16,440 --> 00:35:19,940
Income from writing novels alone
doesn’t bring in that much money for me.

449
00:35:20,960 --> 00:35:23,840
I make 100-200k at best.

450
00:35:25,040 --> 00:35:29,310
New writers entering the scene
earn much more than I do.

451
00:35:31,040 --> 00:35:32,500
Then why are you giving me so much?

452
00:35:39,230 --> 00:35:41,640
Selling novels isn’t
my only source of income.

453
00:35:43,180 --> 00:35:44,320
And more importantly…

454
00:35:47,900 --> 00:35:48,900
I’m already well-off.

455
00:35:57,630 --> 00:35:58,150
So?

456
00:35:59,050 --> 00:36:00,000
How much do you want?

457
00:36:02,170 --> 00:36:02,910
Any amount’s fine.

458
00:36:04,210 --> 00:36:05,550
It’s up to you.

459
00:36:07,890 --> 00:36:09,030
It’s settled then.

460
00:36:16,030 --> 00:36:19,030
My friend’s officially
become a sugar daddy.

461
00:36:32,520 --> 00:36:34,610
Oh no, Ai Mook!

462
00:36:36,680 --> 00:36:37,350
Think.

463
00:36:37,720 --> 00:36:39,020
What do I do?

464
00:36:43,180 --> 00:36:44,250
P’ Vie!

465
00:36:45,620 --> 00:36:46,580
What do I do?

466
00:36:46,660 --> 00:36:48,500
P’ Rak bought some guy
and brought him along!

467
00:36:48,750 --> 00:36:49,760
Really?

468
00:36:50,210 --> 00:36:51,800
What an unusual souvenir this time.

469
00:36:53,430 --> 00:36:55,500
This isn’t funny, P’ Vie.

470
00:36:55,720 --> 00:36:58,050
He’s a man, as in a real man.

471
00:36:58,370 --> 00:36:59,550
A live man in the flesh.

472
00:36:59,860 --> 00:37:01,680
A man who’s got arms and legs.

473
00:37:03,020 --> 00:37:04,490
The kind with the third leg?

474
00:37:04,620 --> 00:37:06,450
P’ Vie!

475
00:37:06,970 --> 00:37:08,160
It’s not funny at all.

476
00:37:08,910 --> 00:37:09,910
Alright, alright.

477
00:37:10,980 --> 00:37:11,970
I'm paying attention now.

478
00:37:12,650 --> 00:37:13,200
What happened?

479
00:37:13,880 --> 00:37:16,020
You went to pick Ai Rak up at the airport.

480
00:37:16,330 --> 00:37:18,890
He showed up and surprised you by saying

481
00:37:18,920 --> 00:37:20,300
“This is the guy I’ve brought with me.”

482
00:37:20,330 --> 00:37:20,940
Right?

483
00:37:22,440 --> 00:37:23,270
Yes.

484
00:37:24,950 --> 00:37:26,510
My friend's such a badass.

485
00:37:28,340 --> 00:37:30,770
This is no laughing matter, P’ Vie.

486
00:37:31,250 --> 00:37:34,580
We don’t know who he is,
where he’s from, or what he’s like.

487
00:37:34,680 --> 00:37:35,780
And… If…

488
00:37:36,730 --> 00:37:39,100
What if he hurts P’ Rak?

489
00:37:40,280 --> 00:37:41,260
What do I do?

490
00:37:42,200 --> 00:37:45,150
I’ve left them alone in there together.

491
00:37:46,640 --> 00:37:48,060
I’m so worried.

492
00:37:49,370 --> 00:37:50,560
Ai Rak’s taken him in?

493
00:37:51,440 --> 00:37:52,500
Yeah.

494
00:37:53,060 --> 00:37:54,860
I don’t know what to do anymore.

495
00:37:58,490 --> 00:37:59,670
I’ve got to see him.

496
00:38:00,760 --> 00:38:03,840
Then I’ll be there tomorrow
after the set wraps.

497
00:38:03,970 --> 00:38:06,200
Umm… Okay.

498
00:38:08,680 --> 00:38:10,480
That’s Ai Vie, my friend.

499
00:38:11,160 --> 00:38:12,320
I’m Mahasamut.

500
00:38:13,780 --> 00:38:15,870
Sawasdee ka, Mr. Tongrak’s boy toy.

501
00:38:17,300 --> 00:38:19,040
So, that’s my title now?

502
00:38:19,720 --> 00:38:20,580
Are you saying it’s not?

503
00:38:21,380 --> 00:38:21,980
It’s not.

504
00:38:22,560 --> 00:38:26,740
You should call me
Daddy Tongrak’s sugar baby.

505
00:38:27,330 --> 00:38:28,280
A more correct term.

506
00:38:31,870 --> 00:38:33,140
You’ve got a good eye.

507
00:38:34,590 --> 00:38:35,190
Thank you.

508
00:38:36,360 --> 00:38:39,140
I guess I do have a few good
qualities, if I’m being honest.

509
00:38:40,790 --> 00:38:42,100
I don’t see what’s good about you.

510
00:38:43,970 --> 00:38:47,440
There, there, feeling jealous
that your brother got stolen?

511
00:38:47,970 --> 00:38:49,600
That’s not what I meant.

512
00:38:52,720 --> 00:38:53,170
Listen.

513
00:38:54,550 --> 00:38:55,740
Don’t be sad, Mook.

514
00:38:56,210 --> 00:38:59,570
It’s something us girls without
a third leg just have to accept.

515
00:39:00,930 --> 00:39:02,340
P’ Vie!

516
00:39:03,030 --> 00:39:06,190
P’ Rak, did you see?
P’ Vie’s teasing me again.

517
00:39:06,220 --> 00:39:06,640
I’m not.

518
00:39:07,810 --> 00:39:09,090
Ai Vie’s right, Mook.

519
00:39:09,480 --> 00:39:10,530
I love you.

520
00:39:11,020 --> 00:39:13,290
But as long as you don’t have…

521
00:39:17,550 --> 00:39:19,270
I can’t love you like that.

522
00:39:19,520 --> 00:39:22,630
P’ Rak, I’m not feeling like that with you.

523
00:39:22,900 --> 00:39:24,730
Is it fun messing with me?

524
00:39:25,400 --> 00:39:26,200
So, it means...

525
00:39:27,710 --> 00:39:29,190
Khun Tongrak can love me.

526
00:39:38,130 --> 00:39:39,180
Because I have that thing…

527
00:39:40,930 --> 00:39:41,670
Khun Tongrak…

528
00:39:46,590 --> 00:39:47,620
can love me.

529
00:39:51,360 --> 00:39:51,740
Sick!

530
00:39:54,380 --> 00:39:57,100
Loving me is easier than dumping me.

531
00:40:03,420 --> 00:40:04,030
What’s it gonna be?

532
00:40:10,610 --> 00:40:11,310
Ridiculous!

533
00:40:19,290 --> 00:40:19,950
Nonsense!

534
00:40:25,840 --> 00:40:26,730
Sweet dreams.

535
00:40:34,640 --> 00:40:35,690
I want to ask you something.

536
00:40:38,480 --> 00:40:39,710
I don’t sell my friend out.

537
00:40:41,080 --> 00:40:42,270
And I don’t take shortcuts.

538
00:40:43,630 --> 00:40:44,640
Then, ask away.

539
00:40:46,050 --> 00:40:47,090
I want to buy some clothes.

540
00:40:47,890 --> 00:40:48,920
